summary: In which I discuss the potentiality for a Tyrus relationship as a result of Cyrus’ growth cycle & blossoming coping skills
title: In which I discuss the potentiality for a Tyrus relationship as a result of Cyrus’ growth cycle & blossoming coping skills
body:
In all honestly….I have ALWAYS imagined Cyrus making the first move and coming onto to TJ first. Not convinced? Check it:

You see, we were introduced to a very anxious kid named Cyrus in the first season. He was a MESS, with puppy-dog eyes and unfathomably deep pockets full of a myriad of literal lifesavers as well as love for a boy named Jonah. Jonah is unaware, as most tween boys are, and latches onto the concept of Andi. Cyrus watches, adapts, cries, but ultimately picks himself up again. I NEED to give my boy credit for that. It is hard as hell to come back from unrequited love, especially if you mix in queer feelings and a burgeoning sexuality to boot. 

But guess what? Cyrus did that. BY HIMSELF. There is no sense in denying that he has a magical and beautiful support system in place- his friends and amazingly blended family is truly a huge part of his ability to cope and grow. However, we cannot deny that it was Cyrus who felt all the feelings and was able to escape Pre-Contemplative stage all the way into a fully accepting, loyal friend that was able to let Jonah go. Not merely for the sake of Andi, but for himself. 

That takes a lot: guts, gumption, coping skills, self-esteem, self-care, and {my favorite} persistent determination to better the self and adapt one’s concept of the self.

Cyrus DID THAT y’all. And it’s clear- we can see by now the very progression I am referring to coming into fruition via his branching out to make new friends, his ability to stick up for himself and his ideals, and his tenacity and kindness to help others through rough patches. 

These skills are incredibly complex, and not often seen within the young tweenage psyche. I appreciate how incredibly nuisanced it is at times, too. It’s not a “hitting you on the head with how changed Cyrus is” thing; it’s more, “character growth is subtle but succinct, and Cyrus actually propels this plot and allows the other characters’ to exhibit growth as well!”.

SOOOOOOO That is why my boy Cyrus is actually far more equipped to broach the subject with TJ first. TJ’s growth curve is beautiful, but it is marked with the kind of resistance and regression common in the growing teen; and as such, is often fraught with misconceptions and the inability to follow through. 

Will Cyrus be anxious to talk to TJ? Of freaking course!!!! I am almost 21 and have been in numerous relationships and have great coping skills, yet I still have much anxiety in initiating a romantic relationship. But when you compare the growth cycles of both Cyrus and TJ, Cyrus is actually (from what we have seen & know) far more advanced, and therefore I believe him to be the catalyst for a potential Tyrus relationship.

Cyrus didn’t want to have feelings for the tall blonde, but how could he not when TJ looked at him like that.
